      "content": "The French Revolution, sparked by social inequality and financial crisis in 1789, saw the Third Estate and the nobility clash at the Estates-General, where representatives of the common people, like Georges Danton, opposed the privileges of the nobility. During the Assembly, Maximilien Robespierre and the Jacobins exerted increasing influence, while King Louis XVI, under pressure, assigned a chair to propel the meetings. By July 14, 1789, Parisians stormed the Bastille, an iconic symbol of royal authority now thrown open to all citizens. This victory sparked a wave of violence and lawlessness as Robespierre's radical faction rose to power, culminating in the Reign of Terror from 1793 to 1794, during which thousands were executed. As the Terror subsided, Napoleon Bonaparte seized the reins in 1799, finally bringing an end to the revolutionary era.",
